<subSubSection id="C334EFADFF83631C73130697FCE04602" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FF83631C73130697FEA943D2" blockId="20.[264,664,924,985]" box="[264,332,959,985]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<figureCitation id="1315A0A3FF83631C73130697FEA943D2" box="[264,332,959,985]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–8" captionStartId="19.[264,382,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[275,1318,317,1748]" captionTargetId="figure-39@19.[265,1324,307,1748]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 5–8. Melaloncha spp., female. Figs. 5–6. Head, anterior. Figs. 7–8. Ovipositor, left lateral. Abbreviations: vfo—ventral fronto­orbital seta, vif—ventral interfrontal seta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5070714" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5070714/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FF83631C73130126FB76445A" blockId="20.[264,1323,1038,1785]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FF83631C73130126FE404423" bold="true" box="[264,421,1038,1064]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Recognition.</emphasis>
This species is distinctive within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C2EC7A5FF83631C717C0127FC0A4423" authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1959" box="[871,1007,1039,1065]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="digitalis">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FF83631C717C0127FC9A4423" box="[871,895,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B95A6034FF83631C71940127FC0A4423" box="[911,1007,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">digitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by its yellow color, medial ventral interfrontal setae, and relatively sparse setae on the ovipositor.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FF83631C73230176FCE04602" blockId="20.[264,1323,1038,1785]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FF83631C73230176FE354473" bold="true" box="[312,464,1118,1144]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
Female (male unknown). Body length 
<quantity id="4CD611C3FF83631C71AE0177FBF34472" box="[949,1046,1119,1145]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
. Frons yellow, bare of setulae except few along eye margin; ocellar triangle black. Frons 0.44 head width. Medial furrow absent. Ocular and genal setae light brown. Flagellomere 1, aristomeres 1, 2 and base of 3 yellow; rest of 3 brown. Palpus white; palpal setulae brown. Scutum yellowishbrown with posterolateral dark spot. Scutellum yellowish­brown with anterolateral round light brown spot. Pleuron yellowish­brown, except basalare dark brown. Legs yellowishbrown. Combined length of foretarsomeres 1.2 length of foretibia. Foretarsal claws simple, unmodified, without basal lobe. 
<collectingRegion id="49EA72C4FF83631C70C5005FFCC4459A" box="[734,801,1399,1425]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Costa</collectingRegion>
0.52 wing length. Halter yellow. Abdominal tergites yellow anteriorly, black posteriorly and with black medially on tergites 2–5. Venter of abdomen yellow. Ovipositor yellow basally, mostly black; elongate, tubular, curved dorsally; with sparse, medium­length setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
